    "body": "### Problem\n\nI use guioptions in my vimrc but even with a guard, I get an error:\n\n```\nError detected while processing C:\\Users\\idbrii\\minimal.vim:\nline    4:\nE519: Option not supported: guioptions+=M\n```\n\n`:h exists()`:\n\n\t\t\t&option-name\tVim option (only checks if it exists, not if it really works)\n\t\t\t+option-name\tVim option that works.\n\nUsing `exists(\"+guioptions\")` works as expected (and returns 1 in gvim), but I don't see why \"exists\" would include \"emits error when used\". Maybe related to #28400?\n\nI ran into this when I tried a 0.11 nightly. I don't have this issue in nvim 0.10.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```vimscript\n\" nvim --clean -u minimal.vim\n\nif exists(\"&guioptions\")\n    \" Must occur before syntax/filetype on (which pathogen triggers).\n    set guioptions+=M\t\t\t\" Don't bother sourcing the menu\nendif\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf the option is not available, then it's not marked as existing.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1723+ge6b84fab83 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1736781742\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 0.0.1576\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWin 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows command prompt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\n`scoop install neovim-nightly` (versions bucket)",
